      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting MCP Clients"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An MCP client is code that opens a connection to an MCP server and calls its tools, reads its resources, and renders its prompts. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "mcp"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " Python library provides "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ClientSession"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " as the uniform interface \u2014 the same session methods work whether the server is a local subprocess (stdio) or a remote HTTP service (SSE). This section covers both connection patterns and the full "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ClientSession"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " API."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "MCP client connection patterns: stdio_client vs sse_client, both feeding into the same ClientSession API with tool/resource/prompt methods"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "ClientSession is transport-agnostic. Switch from stdio to SSE by changing two lines \u2014 the connection context. Every session.call_tool() call and every response type stays identical."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting via stdio"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Use "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "StdioServerParameters"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to specify how to launch the server process, then open the connection with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "stdio_client()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Both are nested async context managers \u2014 the server process lives as long as the inner "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "async with"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " block is open."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\n\nserver_params = StdioServerParameters(\n    command=\"python\",                   # executable\n    args=[\"server.py\"],                 # arguments to pass\n    env={\"GITHUB_TOKEN\": \"ghp_...\"},    # env vars for the subprocess\n)\n\nasync def main():\n    async with stdio_client(server_params) as (read, write):\n        async with ClientSession(read, write) as session:\n            # Handshake: client sends initialize, server responds with capabilities\n            init = await session.initialize()\n            print(f\"Connected to: {init.serverInfo.name}\")\n            print(f\"Supports tools: {'tools' in (init.capabilities or {})}\")\n\n            # List available tools\n            tools_result = await session.list_tools()\n            for tool in tools_result.tools:\n                print(f\"  {tool.name}: {tool.description}\")\n\n            # Call a tool\n            result = await session.call_tool(\"add\", {\"a\": 5, \"b\": 3})\n            if result.isError:\n                print(f\"Tool error: {result.content[0].text}\")\n            else:\n                print(f\"Result: {result.content[0].text}\")\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The outer "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "async with stdio_client(...)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " spawns the subprocess and opens the pipes. The inner "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "async with ClientSession(...)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " sends "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "initialize"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " on entry and cleans up on exit. Never call methods on a session after its context has exited."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting via HTTP + SSE"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For a remote server, replace "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "stdio_client"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "sse_client"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Pass the base URL of the SSE endpoint and any HTTP headers (auth tokens, API keys)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, os\nfrom mcp import ClientSession\nfrom mcp.client.sse import sse_client\n\nasync def main():\n    url = \"https://api.example.com/mcp/sse\"\n    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {os.environ['MCP_TOKEN']}\"}\n\n    async with sse_client(url, headers=headers) as (read, write):\n        async with ClientSession(read, write) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n\n            tools_result = await session.list_tools()\n            print(\"Remote tools:\", [t.name for t in tools_result.tools])\n\n            result = await session.call_tool(\n                \"web_search\", {\"query\": \"model context protocol\"}\n            )\n            print(result.content[0].text)\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "sse_client"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " internally opens a persistent GET to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "/sse"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for receiving events and sends POSTs to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "/message"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " for requests. The session ID is managed automatically."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Full ClientSession API"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tool Methods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Tools have side effects and return content blocks. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "call_tool"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " result always has a "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "content"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list and an "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "isError"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " flag."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# List tools (typically done once after initialize)\ntools_result = await session.list_tools()\nfor tool in tools_result.tools:\n    print(tool.name)          # str\n    print(tool.description)   # str\n    print(tool.inputSchema)   # dict (JSON Schema)\n\n# Call a tool\nresult = await session.call_tool(\n    \"create_issue\",\n    {\"owner\": \"acme\", \"repo\": \"app\", \"title\": \"Bug found\"}\n)\n\n# result.isError is True when the tool reports a failure\nif result.isError:\n    raise RuntimeError(result.content[0].text)\n\n# Multiple content blocks are possible\nfor block in result.content:\n    if block.type == \"text\":\n        print(block.text)\n    elif block.type == \"image\":\n        print(f\"<image: {block.mimeType}, {len(block.data)} bytes>\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Resource Methods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Resources are read-only URI-addressed data. Fetch them when you need reference material the model should read before acting."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# List resources\nresources_result = await session.list_resources()\nfor res in resources_result.resources:\n    print(res.uri, res.name, res.mimeType)\n\n# Read a resource by its URI\nread_result = await session.read_resource(\"myapp://config/schema\")\nfor block in read_result.contents:\n    print(block.text)   # TextContent\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt Methods"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompts are server-side templates rendered with arguments. They return structured message sequences suitable for feeding directly into the LLM."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# List prompts\nprompts_result = await session.list_prompts()\nfor p in prompts_result.prompts:\n    print(p.name, p.description)\n\n# Render a prompt\nprompt_result = await session.get_prompt(\n    \"summarize_pr\",\n    {\"owner\": \"acme\", \"repo\": \"app\", \"pr_number\": \"42\"}\n)\n# Returns messages ready to pass to the LLM\nfor msg in prompt_result.messages:\n    print(msg.role, msg.content.text)   # \"user\" or \"assistant\"\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Connecting to Multiple Servers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agents often aggregate tools from several servers. Open one "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ClientSession"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " per server and collect their tools into a unified catalogue. Prefix tool names with the server name to avoid collisions."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\nfrom mcp.client.sse import sse_client\n\nSERVERS = {\n    \"github\": StdioServerParameters(command=\"python\", args=[\"github_server.py\"]),\n    \"search\": \"https://search-mcp.example.com/sse\",  # remote server\n}\n\nasync def collect_tools(sessions: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build name\u2192(session, tool) mapping with server prefix.\"\"\"\n    all_tools = {}\n    for name, session in sessions.items():\n        result = await session.list_tools()\n        for tool in result.tools:\n            all_tools[f\"{name}__{tool.name}\"] = (session, tool)\n    return all_tools\n\nasync def main():\n    async with (\n        stdio_client(SERVERS[\"github\"]) as (r1, w1),\n        sse_client(SERVERS[\"search\"]) as (r2, w2),\n    ):\n        async with (\n            ClientSession(r1, w1) as gh_session,\n            ClientSession(r2, w2) as search_session,\n        ):\n            await gh_session.initialize()\n            await search_session.initialize()\n\n            sessions = {\"github\": gh_session, \"search\": search_session}\n            tools = await collect_tools(sessions)\n            print(\"All tools:\", list(tools.keys()))\n\n            # Dispatch to the right session\n            tool_name = \"github__list_issues\"\n            session, tool = tools[tool_name]\n            result = await session.call_tool(tool.name, {\"owner\": \"acme\", \"repo\": \"api\"})\n            print(result.content[0].text)\n\nasyncio.run(main())\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Resilience Patterns"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Network and subprocess failures happen. Wrap "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "call_tool"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " with retry logic for transient failures, and distinguish transport errors (exception raised) from tool errors ("
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "isError=True"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ")."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom mcp import ClientSession\nfrom mcp.exceptions import McpError\n\nasync def resilient_call(session: ClientSession, tool: str, args: dict, retries: int = 3):\n    \"\"\"Retry on transport errors; surface tool errors immediately.\"\"\"\n    for attempt in range(retries):\n        try:\n            result = await session.call_tool(tool, args)\n            if result.isError:\n                # Tool-level error \u2014 model should see this, not retry blindly\n                raise RuntimeError(f\"Tool {tool} failed: {result.content[0].text}\")\n            return result\n        except McpError as exc:\n            if attempt == retries - 1:\n                raise\n            wait = 2 ** attempt\n            await asyncio.sleep(wait)\n    raise RuntimeError(f\"Exhausted {retries} retries for {tool}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "McpError"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (from "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "mcp.exceptions"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ") signals a JSON-RPC transport failure \u2014 retrying is safe."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "isError=True"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " means the server understood the request but the tool operation failed. This is domain-level \u2014 retrying the same args without changing them usually does not help."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Subprocess restarts require a new "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "stdio_client"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " context plus "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "initialize()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " again \u2014 there is no reconnect method on a closed session."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Checking Server Capabilities"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "initialize()"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " result carries the server's declared capabilities. Check them before calling optional endpoints like "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "list_resources"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to avoid errors on servers that only expose tools."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "async def inspect(session: ClientSession):\n    init = await session.initialize()\n    caps = init.capabilities or {}\n\n    print(\"Server:\", init.serverInfo.name, init.serverInfo.version)\n    print(\"Protocol:\", init.protocolVersion)\n\n    if \"tools\" in caps:\n        tools = await session.list_tools()\n        print(f\"  {len(tools.tools)} tool(s)\")\n\n    if \"resources\" in caps:\n        resources = await session.list_resources()\n        print(f\"  {len(resources.resources)} resource(s)\")\n\n    if \"prompts\" in caps:\n        prompts = await session.list_prompts()\n        print(f\"  {len(prompts.prompts)} prompt(s)\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrating with an LLM Agent Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In practice, an MCP client feeds tool schemas to the LLM, executes the tools the model requests, and returns results back into the conversation. The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "ClientSession"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " sits in the agent loop's tool execution layer."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio, os, json\nimport anthropic\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\n\nMODEL = \"claude-sonnet-5\"\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef mcp_tools_to_anthropic(tools) -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Convert MCP tool objects to Anthropic API tool dicts.\"\"\"\n    return [\n        {\n            \"name\": t.name,\n            \"description\": t.description,\n            \"input_schema\": t.inputSchema,\n        }\n        for t in tools\n    ]\n\nasync def run_agent(user_message: str):\n    params = StdioServerParameters(\n        command=\"python\", args=[\"github_server.py\"],\n        env={\"GITHUB_TOKEN\": os.environ[\"GITHUB_TOKEN\"]},\n    )\n    async with stdio_client(params) as (r, w):\n        async with ClientSession(r, w) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n            tools_result = await session.list_tools()\n            anthropic_tools = mcp_tools_to_anthropic(tools_result.tools)\n\n            messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}]\n\n            while True:\n                response = client.messages.create(\n                    model=MODEL,\n                    max_tokens=4096,\n                    tools=anthropic_tools,\n                    messages=messages,\n                )\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": response.content})\n\n                # Collect all tool uses in this response\n                tool_uses = [b for b in response.content if b.type == \"tool_use\"]\n                if not tool_uses:\n                    # No more tool calls \u2014 extract final text\n                    for block in response.content:\n                        if hasattr(block, \"text\"):\n                            print(block.text)\n                    break\n\n                # Execute each tool and collect results\n                tool_results = []\n                for tool_use in tool_uses:\n                    mcp_result = await session.call_tool(tool_use.name, dict(tool_use.input))\n                    tool_results.append({\n                        \"type\": \"tool_result\",\n                        \"tool_use_id\": tool_use.id,\n                        \"content\": mcp_result.content[0].text if mcp_result.content else \"\",\n                        \"is_error\": mcp_result.isError,\n                    })\n\n                messages.append({\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": tool_results})\n\nasyncio.run(run_agent(\"List the open issues in acme/api\"))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The loop terminates when the model produces a response with no "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_use"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks \u2014 its final text answer. All tool results are returned as "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "tool_result"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " blocks in the next user turn, following Anthropic's API contract."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Client Connections"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integration tests for MCP clients spawn the actual server subprocess. This verifies the full JSON-RPC round-trip without network dependencies."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# tests/test_client.py\nimport sys, pytest\nfrom mcp import ClientSession, StdioServerParameters\nfrom mcp.client.stdio import stdio_client\n\nSERVER = StdioServerParameters(command=sys.executable, args=[\"server.py\"])\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_initialize():\n    async with stdio_client(SERVER) as (r, w):\n        async with ClientSession(r, w) as session:\n            init = await session.initialize()\n            assert init.serverInfo.name  # server must have a name\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_tool_catalogue_non_empty():\n    async with stdio_client(SERVER) as (r, w):\n        async with ClientSession(r, w) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n            tools = await session.list_tools()\n            assert len(tools.tools) > 0, \"Server exposes no tools\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_call_tool_success():\n    async with stdio_client(SERVER) as (r, w):\n        async with ClientSession(r, w) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n            result = await session.call_tool(\"add\", {\"a\": 10, \"b\": 20})\n            assert not result.isError\n            assert result.content[0].text == \"30\"\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_call_tool_error_flag():\n    \"\"\"Server should return isError=True, not raise, for bad input.\"\"\"\n    async with stdio_client(SERVER) as (r, w):\n        async with ClientSession(r, w) as session:\n            await session.initialize()\n            result = await session.call_tool(\"read_file\", {\"path\": \"../etc/passwd\"})\n            assert result.isError\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Run with "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "pytest tests/ -v --asyncio-mode=auto"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Each test spawns a fresh server subprocess, so tests are fully isolated."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Pitfalls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Calling methods before initialize()."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The session is not ready until "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "initialize()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " completes. Any earlier call will raise or hang."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Using the session after the context exits."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Both context managers must stay open. If the outer "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "stdio_client"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " closes, the subprocess is killed and the session is invalid."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Sharing a session across asyncio tasks without a lock."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClientSession"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is not thread-safe. Use an "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "asyncio.Lock"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " if multiple coroutines call the same session concurrently."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Treating isError=True as a Python exception."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " The call succeeded at the transport level. Log the content and let the model decide whether to retry with different arguments."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Forgetting to prefix tool names when aggregating."
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " Two servers can expose tools with the same name. Always use a "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "server__tool"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " prefix in the model's tool catalogue."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "stdio_client(StdioServerParameters(...))"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for local subprocess servers and "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "sse_client(url, headers=...)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " for remote HTTP servers \u2014 both yield the same "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "(read, write)"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " streams."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "ClientSession"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " is transport-agnostic; all tool/resource/prompt methods are identical regardless of connection type."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Always call "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "await session.initialize()"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " before any other method \u2014 it performs the protocol handshake and returns the server's capabilities."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Distinguish "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "McpError"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (transport failure, retryable) from "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "code"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "result.isError"
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " (tool-level failure, domain-specific)."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Aggregate tools from multiple servers by opening one session per server and prefixing tool names to prevent collisions."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}